The paper proposes a novel deep network embedding model for cross-network node classification, which involves leveraging labeled information from a source network to classify unlabeled nodes in a target network. This problem is related to several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), network embedding (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV) (since the proposed model involves leveraging node attributes). However, given that the paper focuses on developing a deep learning-based approach for network embedding, cs.LG and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
